By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Lagos State – Nigeria’s most populous state and the epicentre of COVID-19 recorded a whopping 712 infections as the Centre for Disease Control confirmed 1,354 new cases on Tuesday. In its report released via twitter handle, the NCDC  said that the new cases were recorded from 21 states including the FCT as follows: Lagos-712FCT-145Plateau-117Kwara-81Kaduna-54Sokoto-39Oyo-38Rivers-37Gombe-21Enugu-20Akwa Ibom-16Bauchi-14Delta-14Ebonyi-13Anambra-9Taraba-8Edo-8Kano-3Osun-2Ekiti-2Ogun-1. The health agency further stated that the total confirmed cases have risen to 92,705 out of which 76,396 patients have been discharged since the index case was  reported in February 27, 2020. It added that a total of 1,319 lives have been lost to COVID-19 related complications from various isolation facilities in Nigeria. According to the report, the breakdown of the total confirmed cases for each of the 36 states including the FCT is as follows: By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) -  Lagos State, the epicentre of COVID-19 in Nigeria recorded 106 infections on Friday as the Centre for Disease Control confirmed 170 new cases of the novel virus. This renewed upsurge in number of infections in Lagos may not be unconnected with the large… October 31, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The latest COVID-19 report released by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has it that Lagos State, the epicentre of the novel virus, accounted for 642 infections as the health agency confirmed 1,074 new cases on Monday. According to the report released via… January 2, 2021 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Nigeria on Saturday recorded 110 new cases of COVID-19 infections, bringing the total confirmed cases in the country to 67,330, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has said. This is also as the Centre has informed that a total of 62,819 patients have… November 29, 2020 In "Top Stories"